### Configuration for linux desktop (shell access)

# cat apps/shell/env:

OOD_NO_CSRF=false
OOD_SSH_HOSTS="localhost"
NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0
NODE_ENV=production
NODE_PATH=/usr/bin/node
OOD_SSH_FLAGS="-o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null"
OOD_SSHHOST_ALLOWLIST=login02:login01
OOD_SHELL_ORIGIN_CHECK='off'
OOD_NAVBAR_BG_COLOR="#002d54"
OOD_DASHBOARD_TITLE="Param Rudra terminal"


### 1. Update 'ood_portal.yml'

Open your configuration file (usually at `/etc/ood/config/ood_portal.yml`) and ensure your session cookies are set to `Lax` or `None`.

If you are using **HTTPS** (highly recommended), set it to `None`:

# vim /etc/ood/config/ood_portal.yml
# This ensures cookies are sent along with the cross-tab request to the shell
lua_set_env:
  OOD_SESSION_COOKIE_SAMESITE: "None"
  OOD_SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE: "On"


In ondemand.d/rudra.yml
---
v2:
  metadata:
    title: "Param Rudra cluster"
  login:
    host: "localhost" # Connects to the local login node
  job:
    adapter: "slurm"  # This enables the "Shell" menu item in OOD
    bin: "/usr/bin"          # Path where 'sbatch', 'squeue' live
    conf: "/etc/slurm/slurm.conf"
    copy_environment: false
    strict_host_checking: false
  batch_connect:
    vnc:
      script_wrapper: "export PATH=$PATH:/opt/TurboVNC/bin; %s"
    ssh_allow: true
